---
description: Require full unit test run before finishing commit-push-done workflow
alwaysApply: true
---

When executing the `commit-push-done` command workflow:

1. Run the full unit test suite for the repository before the workflow is considered complete.
2. Never proceed to merge/push cleanup steps if any unit test fails.
3. If the repository test command is ambiguous, stop and ask the user for the exact unit test command, then run it.

Do not mark the workflow as successful unless all unit tests have passed in the current branch state.
